title: Grateful Dead Live at Pine Knob Music Theater on 1980-08-27
lineage: Dat -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.1 -> FLAC
description:
Set 1

Promised Land, They Love Each Other, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Minglewood Blues, Althea, Looks Like Rain, Big Railroad Blues, Feel Like A Stranger

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, CC Rider, High Time, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Super Crisp SBD The first thing I noticed was how crisp the vocals were on this SBD.  I felt like I was embedded in their microphones and the boys' mouths were just inches away.  I enjoy shows from this period right before the acoustic shows, like Lewiston and the Mississippi River Festival. I am adding this show to that list.   The China Rider is great. Garcia belts out "I wish I was a headlight....." with mucho gusto.  Phil is low in the mix in the first set but is more present in the second set. Thanks CM for uploading this high quality show!
Vocals are off Probably not much CM could have done with this one, but a thank-you for the try. Too bad b/c it mars what could have been a nice show.
- Can't listen to it. The instruments are buried.

Phil ! Phil Is Deeply Engaged In The Music This Night. (No Pun Intended) Close Your Eyes And Listen To Phil And Let The Rest Of The Band Fall Into Place Around Him. No Real "Bombs" Just Incessant Liquid Thunder With No Let Up. Always A Good Ride.
